00:18:00,352 --> 00:18:01,031
But...

289
00:18:01,032 --> 00:18:02,192
The subway doesn't operate
anymore at this hour.

290
00:18:02,193 --> 00:18:03,192
Where could she have gone?

291
00:18:03,193 --> 00:18:04,152
Alright. No need for change.

292
00:18:04,153 --> 00:18:05,392
Will anything happen to her?

293
00:18:05,393 --> 00:18:06,152
You...

294
00:18:06,153 --> 00:18:07,472
- What could happen?
- Don't worry.

295
00:18:07,473 --> 00:18:08,192
Nothing will happen.

296
00:18:08,193 --> 00:18:08,952
Both of you go back first.

297
00:18:08,953 --> 00:18:10,031
I'll go check again.

298
00:18:10,032 --> 00:18:11,152
No, Haiyang,

299
00:18:11,153 --> 00:18:12,311
I'll go with you.

300
00:18:12,312 --> 00:18:13,522
Dad, Mum!

301
00:18:14,193 --> 00:18:15,123
You...

302
00:18:15,312 --> 00:18:16,712
Why are you here?

303
00:18:16,713 --> 00:18:17,672
What's going on?

304
00:18:17,673 --> 00:18:18,672
Why aren't you answering your phone?

305
00:18:18,673 --> 00:18:20,271
We were so worried!

306
00:18:20,272 --> 00:18:21,282
Where have you been?

307
00:18:21,352 --> 00:18:23,123
Why couldn't we reach you?

308
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:24,511
Oh, I...

309
00:18:24,512 --> 00:18:25,511
I realized I lost my phone

310
00:18:25,512 --> 00:18:26,912
after leaving the subway,

311
00:18:26,913 --> 00:18:28,282
so I went back to look for it.

312
00:18:28,312 --> 00:18:29,311
Where's your phone then?

313
00:18:29,312 --> 00:18:32,071
I was too tired
and fell asleep on the way.

314
00:18:32,072 --> 00:18:32,952
I don't know where I lost it.

315
00:18:32,953 --> 00:18:34,082
So you lost your phone?

316
00:18:34,112 --> 00:18:36,111
If it's lost, just let it go. You are...

317
00:18:36,112 --> 00:18:37,551
If it's lost,
just ignore it.

318
00:18:37,552 --> 00:18:37,992
You...

319
00:18:37,993 --> 00:18:39,802
I have to find it if it's lost.

320
00:18:39,913 --> 00:18:41,872
Dad, Mum, don't worry.

321
00:18:41,873 --> 00:18:43,912
As long as she's back safely,
that's what matters,

322
00:18:43,913 --> 00:18:44,511
right?

323
00:18:44,512 --> 00:18:45,243
Hold on.

324
00:18:45,352 --> 00:18:46,562
Why are you still
calling them Dad and Mum?

325
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:47,511
We're divorced.

326
00:18:47,512 --> 00:18:48,802
It's not appropriate.

327
00:18:49,153 --> 00:18:49,872
But

328
00:18:49,873 --> 00:18:51,111
Haiyang has been calling us
that way for so long.

329
00:18:51,112 --> 00:18:51,831
He's used to it.

330
00:18:51,832 --> 00:18:52,432
It takes time for him...

331
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:53,751
That's not the case.

332
00:18:53,752 --> 00:18:55,031
We're already divorced.
He shouldn't call you that way.

333
00:18:55,032 --> 00:18:55,632
He's used to it already.

334
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:56,483
It's been a very long time.

335
00:18:56,512 --> 00:18:57,751
There are no outsiders here.

336
00:18:57,752 --> 00:18:58,472
He should change it.

337
00:18:58,473 --> 00:19:00,152
But, you should give
him time to change it.

338
00:19:00,153 --> 00:19:01,031
I can't tolerate it.

339
00:19:01,032 --> 00:19:02,031
- Yeah, you're right.
- Let him change.

340
00:19:02,032 --> 00:19:02,751
Yeah, you're right.

341
00:19:02,752 --> 00:19:03,551
What makes you uncomfortable?

342
00:19:03,552 --> 00:19:04,071
She's right.

343
00:19:04,072 --> 00:19:06,311
Mum, don't worry. Oops...

344
00:19:06,312 --> 00:19:07,163
It's fine.

345
00:19:07,352 --> 00:19:08,163
My god.

346
00:19:10,352 --> 00:19:12,082
Uncle, Auntie,

347
00:19:12,592 --> 00:19:14,963
it's late now.

348
00:19:15,153 --> 00:19:16,522
Let me take you home.

349
00:19:16,873 --> 00:19:18,163
It's too dangerous to take a tricycle.

350
00:19:18,193 --> 00:19:18,872
No, no need.

351
00:19:18,873 --> 00:19:20,232
My dad and mum will stay here tonight.

352
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:20,791
No.

353
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:21,511
Wait, your mum and I

354
00:19:21,512 --> 00:19:22,712
can go back by our tricycle.

355
00:19:22,713 --> 00:19:24,392
It's late now. Let's go inside.

356
00:19:24,393 --> 00:19:25,511
Deng Haiyang, what's wrong with you?

357
00:19:25,512 --> 00:19:26,111
You overreacted,

358
00:19:26,112 --> 00:19:26,923
and called my parents here.

359
00:19:26,993 --> 00:19:28,672
It's us who called him.

360
00:19:28,673 --> 00:19:30,511
We called him.

361
00:19:30,512 --> 00:19:32,152
Haiyang, you take a good rest.

362
00:19:32,153 --> 00:19:33,311
No problem. I will.

363
00:19:33,312 --> 00:19:34,031
Be careful on the road.

364
00:19:34,032 --> 00:19:34,632
Don't worry.

365
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:35,672
Sorry for the trouble.

366
00:19:35,673 --> 00:19:36,511
No trouble at all.

367
00:19:36,512 --> 00:19:37,992
You just watched too many dramas.

368
00:19:37,993 --> 00:19:40,163
Stop watching all those things online.

369
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:41,152
What do you mean by that?

370
00:19:41,153 --> 00:19:42,152
You should stop reading

371
00:19:42,153 --> 00:19:43,392
all that nonsense online.

372
00:19:43,393 --> 00:19:44,632
I can't go missing.

373
00:19:44,633 --> 00:19:45,791
Take care.

374
00:19:45,792 --> 00:19:46,562
Haiyang,

375
00:19:46,633 --> 00:19:47,712
be safe on your way home.

376
00:19:47,713 --> 00:19:48,392
Alright.

377
00:19:48,393 --> 00:19:48,992
Alright, go in.

378
00:19:48,993 --> 00:19:50,071
Why are you like this?

379
00:19:50,072 --> 00:19:51,912
Why did you come out late at night?

380
00:19:51,913 --> 00:19:52,511
If you come out at this late hour,

381
00:19:52,512 --> 00:19:53,762
I couldn't relax as well.

382
00:19:55,393 --> 00:19:56,683
Alright.

383
00:20:06,552 --> 00:20:08,031
Listen, from now on,

384
00:20:08,032 --> 00:20:09,802
don't involve Deng Haiyang
in my matters.

385
00:20:10,072 --> 00:20:10,791
We...

386
00:20:10,792 --> 00:20:11,712
We just

387
00:20:11,713 --> 00:20:12,472
had no choice.

388
00:20:12,473 --> 00:20:13,511
We were worried.

389
00:20:13,512 --> 00:20:14,751
Well, no matter what,
don't call him again.

390
00:20:14,752 --> 00:20:15,232
What's the matter?

391
00:20:15,233 --> 00:20:15,831
I'm an adult.

392
00:20:15,832 --> 00:20:16,831
I'm not going to go missing.

393
00:20:16,832 --> 00:20:17,643
You see...

394
00:20:18,993 --> 00:20:20,762
You come home too late.

395
00:20:20,792 --> 00:20:22,351
It's very dangerous.

396
00:20:22,352 --> 00:20:24,232
Didn't you come across the news?

397
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,392
These days, young women

398
00:20:25,393 --> 00:20:27,203
go missing after work.

399
00:20:27,512 --> 00:20:29,551
By the time they're found,

400
00:20:29,552 --> 00:20:30,912
it's often too late.

401
00:20:30,913 --> 00:20:31,551
Alright, stop it.

402
00:20:31,552 --> 00:20:32,831
Don't say things like that.

403
00:20:32,832 --> 00:20:33,472
It's too grim.

404
00:20:33,473 --> 00:20:34,632
Don't tell her that.

405
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:35,952
I'm just warning her to be cautious.

406
00:20:35,953 --> 00:20:37,071
It will scare her,

407
00:20:37,072 --> 00:20:38,082
and she'll be even more worried.

408
00:20:38,153 --> 00:20:39,602
She'll be more vigilant then.

409
00:20:39,913 --> 00:20:41,351
Alright, stop it!

410
00:20:41,352 --> 00:20:42,392
I got it!

411
00:20:42,393 --> 00:20:43,762
I'll be careful.

412
00:20:44,913 --> 00:20:46,483
She thinks we're being too controlling.

413
00:20:46,673 --> 00:20:48,511
It's just that we called Deng Haiyang,

414
00:20:48,512 --> 00:20:49,643
and she wasn't happy.

415
00:20:49,673 --> 00:20:51,163
That's right,
you shouldn't find Deng Haiyang.

416
00:20:51,913 --> 00:20:52,672
Why are you just standing there?

417
00:20:52,673 --> 00:20:53,591
Wash up and go to bed.

418
00:20:53,592 --> 00:20:54,643
It’s late.

419
00:20:54,752 --> 00:20:56,111
We’re not staying.

420
00:20:56,112 --> 00:20:56,632
We're heading back.

421
00:20:56,633 --> 00:20:57,271
We’re not staying here.

422
00:20:57,272 --> 00:20:57,912
We just wanted to check on you

423
00:20:57,913 --> 00:20:58,511
and make sure you’re safe.

424
00:20:58,512 --> 00:20:58,952
That's right.

425
00:20:58,953 --> 00:21:00,602
Why leave? It’s already so late.

426
00:21:00,953 --> 00:21:01,723
Alright.

427
00:21:01,792 --> 00:21:02,842
Listen, after this,

428
00:21:03,032 --> 00:21:04,192
you have to come home early after work,

429
00:21:04,193 --> 00:21:05,723
and don't go out at night.

430
00:21:05,953 --> 00:21:06,791
When you're at home,

431
00:21:06,792 --> 00:21:08,762
make sure you lock the door properly.

432
00:21:09,072 --> 00:21:10,042
Alright.

433
00:21:10,112 --> 00:21:11,111
She was having an overtime.

434
00:21:11,112 --> 00:21:11,872
She was busy,

435
00:21:11,873 --> 00:21:12,923
and not going out to have fun.

436
00:21:12,993 --> 00:21:14,632
Don't work overtime after this.

437
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:15,351
Alright, I won't do it anymore.

438
00:21:15,352 --> 00:21:16,872
It's fine to let them cut the bonus.

439
00:21:16,873 --> 00:21:18,192
Do you think she has a choice

440
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:19,591
to say no to working overtime?

441
00:21:19,592 --> 00:21:20,351
I let her come home earlier.

442
00:21:20,352 --> 00:21:20,831
Stop it.

443
00:21:20,832 --> 00:21:21,672
I get it. Stop nagging me.

444
00:21:21,673 --> 00:21:22,362
We're leaving.

445
00:21:22,433 --> 00:21:23,031
Alright.

446
00:21:23,032 --> 00:21:23,992
You two be safe on the way home.

447
00:21:23,993 --> 00:21:24,392
Call me

448
00:21:24,393 --> 00:21:25,232
when you get home.

449
00:21:25,233 --> 00:21:26,111
We'll be fine.

450
00:21:26,112 --> 00:21:26,831
Lock the door properly.

451
00:21:26,832 --> 00:21:27,511
Lock the door properly.

452
00:21:27,512 --> 00:21:29,282
Your phone was lost, wasn't it?

453
00:21:30,473 --> 00:21:31,031
Oh yeah.

454
00:21:31,032 --> 00:21:31,672
You're right.

455
00:21:31,673 --> 00:21:33,042
We'll be fine, don't worry.

456
00:21:33,352 --> 00:21:34,282
Be careful

457
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:35,591
Lock the door properly.

458
00:21:35,592 --> 00:21:37,042
I'll listen outside
if you lock it properly or not.

459
00:21:38,352 --> 00:21:39,362
Lock it.

460
00:22:44,832 --> 00:22:46,923
Why can't you sleep again?

461
00:22:47,913 --> 00:22:49,042
You haven't slept too?

462
00:22:49,393 --> 00:22:50,723
I was thinking...

463
00:22:52,873 --> 00:22:54,042
Maybe Xiang Zhong

464
00:22:55,552 --> 00:22:56,643
should live in Shanghai.

465
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:58,002
What do you think?

466
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:02,002
Living at Xiang Qian's place
isn't appropriate.

467
00:23:03,312 --> 00:23:05,322
Can't you think a little?

468
00:23:07,272 --> 00:23:08,712
If Xiang Zhong moves to Shanghai,

469
00:23:08,713 --> 00:23:10,443
she can stay alone too.

470
00:23:11,993 --> 00:23:13,602
But, we can't afford

471
00:23:13,713 --> 00:23:15,403
to buy a house in Shanghai.

472
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:16,831
Well.

473
00:23:16,832 --> 00:23:17,672
It's difficult discussing
anything with you

474
00:23:17,673 --> 00:23:19,672
when you're half-asleep.

475
00:23:19,673 --> 00:23:20,723
You're really...

476
00:23:21,112 --> 00:23:23,282
Sleep faster.

477
00:23:24,913 --> 00:23:26,362
Fine, I sleep.

478
00:23:39,393 --> 00:23:41,123
If only our three daughters

479
00:23:41,153 --> 00:23:43,643
could be like you...

480
00:24:36,352 --> 00:24:37,163
Zhong.

481
00:24:37,953 --> 00:24:38,883
Good morning.

482
00:24:39,312 --> 00:24:40,322
Here,

483
00:24:41,873 --> 00:24:43,042
you should keep the car for yourself.

484
00:24:43,112 --> 00:24:44,802
I parked it at the lot over there.

485
00:24:45,713 --> 00:24:46,562
I...

486
00:24:46,792 --> 00:24:48,163
Forget it. I'm not good at driving.

487
00:24:48,673 --> 00:24:49,632
You have a driver's license.

488
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:50,271
You just have to get used to it,

489
00:24:50,272 --> 00:24:51,392
and driving yourself

490
00:24:51,393 --> 00:24:53,163
would ease your parents' minds.

491
00:24:54,433 --> 00:24:55,403
Alright.

492
00:24:58,193 --> 00:24:59,952
Aren't you going to the training class?

493
00:24:59,953 --> 00:25:00,723
Not leaving?

494
00:25:01,072 --> 00:25:02,282
I'm fine, no rush.

495
00:25:02,592 --> 00:25:03,522
Otherwise,

496
00:25:03,953 --> 00:25:05,472
we'd be caught
in the same subway carriage.

497
00:25:05,473 --> 00:25:07,042
I wouldn't know what to talk about.

498
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:10,123
You could just not talk.

499
00:25:33,460 --> 00:25:35,750
(Divorce Matters)

500
00:25:43,312 --> 00:25:44,243
Hello, dad.

501
00:25:49,112 --> 00:25:49,712
Alright.

502
00:25:49,713 --> 00:25:51,403
Come meet me at noon.

503
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,680
(Divorce Matters
1. Confirm the babysitter )

504
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:05,200
(2. Confirm required documents
with Attorney Wu for child's surname change.)

505
00:26:15,032 --> 00:26:16,723
Xiang Qian always listens to you.

506
00:26:17,473 --> 00:26:18,071
You should...

507
00:26:18,072 --> 00:26:19,403
What should I say?

508
00:26:19,673 --> 00:26:21,042
When you bring it up,

509
00:26:21,352 --> 00:26:22,883
she would agree with you.

510
00:26:24,153 --> 00:26:24,632
Xiang Qian.

511
00:26:24,633 --> 00:26:25,963
Why is mum here too?

512
00:26:26,673 --> 00:26:29,071
Your dad said this is important.

513
00:26:29,072 --> 00:26:30,282
Very important.

514
00:26:30,512 --> 00:26:32,243
What's so important?

515
00:26:33,072 --> 00:26:34,403
Go ahead and tell her.

516
00:26:34,673 --> 00:26:35,723
Alright, let me start.

517
00:26:36,913 --> 00:26:37,751
Xiang Zhong has been

518
00:26:37,752 --> 00:26:39,923
going back and forth
between Shanghai and Kunshan,

519
00:26:40,032 --> 00:26:42,123
Sometimes, she has to work overtime

520
00:26:42,272 --> 00:26:43,591
and go home late.

521
00:26:43,592 --> 00:26:45,802
Your dad worries about her safety.

522
00:26:45,953 --> 00:26:47,963
Your mum, too, feels worried
about her safety.

523
00:26:49,473 --> 00:26:50,791
What does this mean?

524
00:26:50,792 --> 00:26:51,952
We thought about renting a place

525
00:26:51,953 --> 00:26:53,443
near her company.

526
00:26:53,473 --> 00:26:54,071
Oh my god!

527
00:26:54,072 --> 00:26:55,311
The housing near her company

528
00:26:55,312 --> 00:26:57,243
isn't cheap.

529
00:26:57,433 --> 00:26:58,562
Let her have a look.

530
00:27:01,032 --> 00:27:01,791
- Take a look.
- We already found one.

531
00:27:01,792 --> 00:27:02,923
- This place.
- You see.

532
00:27:03,352 --> 00:27:04,723
The window faces the sun.

533
00:27:04,832 --> 00:27:05,723
This is great, right?

534
00:27:05,792 --> 00:27:06,591
This place

535
00:27:06,592 --> 00:27:07,952
is two subway stops

536
00:27:07,953 --> 00:27:09,042
from Xiang Zhong's office

537
00:27:09,153 --> 00:27:11,602
and has 24-hour security.

538
00:27:12,552 --> 00:27:13,723
How much is it?

539
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:16,082
3,500 yuan.

540
00:27:16,832 --> 00:27:17,923
3,500 yuan?

541
00:27:18,352 --> 00:27:19,311
No way.

542
00:27:19,312 --> 00:27:20,643
You both must have been swindled.

543
00:27:20,752 --> 00:27:21,392
You see.

544
00:27:21,393 --> 00:27:22,672
The housing near her company

545
00:27:22,673 --> 00:27:24,432
starts at 5,000 yuan minimum.

546
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:26,042
No, it's 3,500 yuan.

547
00:27:26,072 --> 00:27:26,751
The owner

548
00:27:26,752 --> 00:27:28,282
lives abroad

549
00:27:28,312 --> 00:27:29,723
and doesn't know the market,

550
00:27:29,752 --> 00:27:31,111
so they don't raise the rent

551
00:27:31,112 --> 00:27:32,723
and have been renting at this rate.

552
00:27:32,752 --> 00:27:35,123
This room just became available.

553
00:27:35,393 --> 00:27:37,002
We're so lucky.

554
00:27:40,352 --> 00:27:41,712
Whether it's 3,500 yuan

555
00:27:41,713 --> 00:27:42,831
or 5,000 yuan,

556
00:27:42,832 --> 00:27:44,511
it's up to Xiang Zhong's will.

557
00:27:44,512 --> 00:27:45,282
Am I right?

558
00:27:45,433 --> 00:27:46,232
You should

559
00:27:46,233 --> 00:27:47,511
ask her

560
00:27:47,512 --> 00:27:48,672
if she's willing

561
00:27:48,673 --> 00:27:50,403
to pay for the rent each month.

562
00:27:51,713 --> 00:27:53,031
Of course, we can't let Xiang Zhong

563
00:27:53,032 --> 00:27:54,203
pay for it.

564
00:27:54,312 --> 00:27:55,322
We'll cover it.

565
00:27:55,433 --> 00:27:56,403
Yes, exactly.

566
00:27:59,072 --> 00:27:59,883
Fine.

567
00:28:00,312 --> 00:28:01,192
Which agency is this?

568
00:28:01,193 --> 00:28:02,723
I'll talk to them this afternoon.

569
00:28:03,873 --> 00:28:05,443
No need.

570
00:28:05,512 --> 00:28:07,082
Deposit and three month's rent paid.

571
00:28:07,193 --> 00:28:09,002
We've already signed for it.

572
00:28:09,473 --> 00:28:11,163
You already signed?

573
00:28:11,272 --> 00:28:12,842
So why are you discussing it with me?

